metadata.name: The rain under the bay
metadata.description: It was at the very end of 2019. My wife and I were sitting on the beach under the casuarinas and drawing. And right in front of us, across the bay, there was a powerful downpour. It was dry and calm in the place where we sat, but the elements were raging a few hundred meters from us. The huge rain was approaching. There was a strange feeling of sadness. The feeling that the present happy moment is short-lived. That something huge and frightening is approaching ...
